Code:
```go
var params []interface{}
if jrpcReq, err := req.JsonRpcRequest(); err == nil && jrpcReq != nil {
    params = jrpcReq.Params
}
```
This runs unconditionally on every Match invocation. JsonRpcRequest is cheap on the warm path (atomic.Pointer.Load), but: (a) it's still a virtual call + atomic + branch per Match, and (b) the vast majority of failsafe matchers in the wild have no Params constraint (params-based matching is the new feature - existing converted-from-legacy configs never use it).
